SIMPLE: infra-red
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Infra-red
<hw>In`fra-red"</hw></mhw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Infra-</ets> + <ets>red</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Physics)</fld> <def>Lying outside the visible spectrum
at its red end; -- said of rays having a longer wavelength (and thus
less refrangible) than the extreme red rays, specifically those
electromagnetic waves having a wavelength of between 700 nanometers and
1 millimeter.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>relating to, using, or producing infrared
radiation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>affected by infrared radiation; <as>as,
<ex>infrared</ex> detector; <ex>infrared</ex> film</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Infrared Radiation</ent>⟦br⟧
